<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN338-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. kuṉṟūr kiḻār makaṉār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div> 
    <div xml:id="PN338">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>ērparanta vayaṉīr paranta ceṟuvi</l>
<l>ṉeṉmalinta maṉaippoṉ malinta maṟukiṟ</l>
<l>paṭuvaṇ ṭārkkum paṉmalark kāvi</l>
<l>ṉeṭuvē ḷātaṉ pōntai yaṉṉa</l>
<l>peruñcī raruṅkoṇ ṭiyaḷē karuñciṉai</l>
<l>vēmpu mārum pōntaiyu mūṉṟum</l>
<l>malainta ceṉṉiya raṇinta villar</l>
<l>koṟṟa vēntar variṉun taṟṟaka</l>
<l>vaṇaṅkārk kīkuva ṉallaṉ vaṇṭōṭṭup</l>
<l>piṇaṅkukatirk kaḻaṉi nāppa ṇēmuṟ</l>
<l>ṟuṇaṅkukala ṉāḻiyiṟ ṟōṉṟu</l>
<l>mōreyiṉ maṉṉa ṉorumaṭa makaḷē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Like the Pōntai of Neṭuvēḷātaṉ, (4)</l>
<l>with paddy fields spread with ploughs, fields spread with water, (1)</l>
<l>houses abounding in paddy, streets abounding in gold, (2)</l>
<l>groves of many blossoms where the descending bees hum (3)</l>
<l>she of great excellence will be a lot difficult to [take]. (5a-c)  </l>
<l>Having heads that wear black-branched Neem, </l>
<l>laburnum and palmyra, having decorated bows (5d-7)</l>
<l>even if those victorious kings come, he won’t </l>
<l>give [her] to one who does not bow [to him] as it suits him, (8-9c)</l>
<l>the king with a single fortress,  (12ab)</l>
<l>that appears like a dry ship on the ocean, (11)</l>
<l>well-protected among [his] paddy fields with ears intertwining with generous leaves, (9d-10)</l>
	[and] one single youthful daughter. (12cd)
</lg>
    </div>
